---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import ContactEmail from '../components/ContactEmail.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';

const updated = new Date(SITE.lastPolicyUpdate).toLocaleDateString('en-US', {
  year: 'numeric',
  month: 'long',
  day: 'numeric',
});
---

<PageLayout
  title="Privacy Policy: Data, Cookies & Your Rights"
  description="How Ramen Guide collects, uses, and protects your personal information, including your rights under the GDPR and CCPA."
  lastUpdated={updated}
>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Ramen Guide</strong> ("we", "us", "the
    publication") collects, uses, and shares information when you visit
    <a href={SITE.url}>{SITE.url}</a> (the "Site"). We aim to collect as little personal data as
    possible.
  </p>

  <h2>Information we collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Information you give us.</strong> If you email us at
      <ContactEmail />, we receive your email address
      and the contents of your message.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Newsletter subscription.</strong> If you subscribe to our email updates, we collect
      your email address and the date and consent record of your sign-up, so we can send you new-post
      notifications. You can unsubscribe at any time using the link in every email.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Information collected automatically.</strong> Like most websites, our hosting and
      third-party services may log technical data such as your IP address, browser type, device
      information, referring pages, and the pages you view. This is used to operate and secure the
      Site and to understand aggregate usage.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Cookies and similar technologies.</strong> Cookies may be set by us and by third
      parties (see below) for functionality, measurement, and advertising.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Advertising and third-party partners</h2>
  <p>
    We intend to display advertising on the Site. Third-party vendors, including
    <strong>Google</strong>, may use cookies and similar technologies to serve ads based on your
    prior visits to this and other websites.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads to you based on
      your visits to the Site and/or other sites on the Internet.
    </li>
    <li>
      You may opt out of personalised advertising by visiting
      <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Google Ads Settings</a>,
      and from third-party vendors at
      <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">aboutads.info</a> or
      <a href="https://www.youronlinechoices.eu/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">youronlinechoices.eu</a>.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Analytics</h2>
  <p>
    We use the following analytics services to understand how visitors use the Site and to improve
    our content:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Google Analytics</strong> (provided by Google) measures aggregate traffic such as page
      views, sessions, and approximate location, using cookies. See
      <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Microsoft Clarity</strong> (provided by Microsoft) captures how visitors interact with
      the Site through behavioural metrics, heatmaps, and session replay, which help us diagnose
      usability issues. Clarity uses cookies and similar technologies, and Microsoft may use the data
      it collects as described in the
      <a href="https://privacy.microsoft.com/privacystatement" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Microsoft Privacy Statement</a>.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Where analytics or advertising rely on consent, we will obtain it as required by applicable law.
  </p>

  <h2>Email newsletter</h2>
  <p>
    Our email updates are delivered through <strong>Kit</strong> (formerly ConvertKit), a
    third-party email service provider that stores subscriber email addresses and sign-up details on
    our behalf and processes them solely to send the notifications you requested. We do not share
    your email address with advertisers. You can unsubscribe at any time using the link in every
    email, and Kit's handling of your data is described in
    <a href="https://kit.com/privacy" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Kit's Privacy Policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>How we use information</h2>
  <p>
    We use information to operate, maintain, and secure the Site; to respond to your messages; to
    measure and improve our content; and to display and measure advertising. We do not sell your
    personal information for money.
  </p>

  <h2>Your rights under the GDPR (EEA/UK)</h2>
  <p>
    If you are in the European Economic Area or the United Kingdom, you have the right to access,
    correct, delete, restrict, or object to the processing of your personal data, and the right to
    data portability and to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority. Our legal bases for
    processing are your consent (which you may withdraw at any time), our legitimate interests in
    operating the Site, and compliance with legal obligations.
  </p>

  <h2>Your rights under the CCPA (California)</h2>
  <p>
    If you are a California resident, you have the right to know what personal information we
    collect, to request deletion, to opt out of the "sale" or "sharing" of personal information as
    those terms are defined by the CCPA, and not to be discriminated against for exercising these
    rights. We do not sell personal information for monetary consideration; some advertising and
    analytics cookie activity may constitute "sharing" under the CCPA, which you can limit using the
    opt-out links above.
  </p>

  <h2>Data retention</h2>
  <p>
    We keep personal information only for as long as necessary for the purposes described here or as
    required by law. Email correspondence is retained for as long as needed to handle your inquiry,
    and newsletter subscriber data is retained until you unsubscribe.
  </p>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>
    The Site is not directed to children under 16, and we do not knowingly collect personal
    information from them.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy from time to time. Material changes will be reflected by the "Last
    updated" date above.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    To exercise any right or ask a privacy question, email
    <ContactEmail />.
  </p>
</PageLayout>
